       displaying  the Unix manual pages (_m_a_n _p_a_g_e_s), such that it can be used
       as a replacement for a mmaann(1) program.  Moreover, compressed files that
       can be handled by ggzziipp(1) or bbzziipp22(1) are decompressed on-the-fly.

       The  normal usage is quite simple by supplying a file name or name of a
       _m_a_n _p_a_g_e without further options.  But the  option  handling  has  many
